<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Optional on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/optional/</link><description>Recent content in Optional on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/optional/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_optional_access - empty optional</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-optional-access/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-optional-access/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stdbad_optional_access---empty-optional"&gt;std::bad_optional_access - empty optional&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;std::bad_optional_access&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you call &lt;code&gt;std::optional::value()&lt;/code&gt; on an empty optional.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: value() on empty optional
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;optional&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; opt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; opt.value(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: * operator on empty optional
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;optional&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; opt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;opt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// undefined behavior
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Optional not set conditionally
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;optional&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; name;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (condition) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string n &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; name.value(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws if condition was false
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-has_value"&gt;Fix 1: Check has_value()&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;optional&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; opt &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; get_value();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (opt.has_value()) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; opt.value();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-value_or"&gt;Fix 2: Use value_or()&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; opt.value_or(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// returns 0 if empty
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-operator-with-check"&gt;Fix 3: Use operator* with check&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (opt) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;opt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-variant-access/"&gt;std::bad_variant_access&lt;/a&gt; — wrong variant type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/any-cast-error/"&gt;std::bad_any_cast&lt;/a&gt; — any_cast failure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-function-call/"&gt;std::bad_function_call&lt;/a&gt; — empty function.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::optional Error — Optional Access Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/optional-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/optional-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdoptional-error--optional-access-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::optional Error — Optional Access Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::optional&lt;/code&gt; error occurs when calling &lt;code&gt;value()&lt;/code&gt; or dereferencing an optional that does not contain a value. This throws &lt;code&gt;std::bad_optional_access&lt;/code&gt;. The error happens when code assumes a value exists without checking first.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdoptional-errors-occur"&gt;Why std::optional Errors Occur&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include calling &lt;code&gt;value()&lt;/code&gt; without checking &lt;code&gt;has_value()&lt;/code&gt;, dereferencing a default-constructed optional, optional becoming empty after &lt;code&gt;reset()&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;operator=&lt;/code&gt;, and not handling the empty case when using optional return values.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Swift Error — Force Unwrap Crash</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/force-unwrap/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/force-unwrap/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="force-unwrap--unexpectedly-found-nil"&gt;Force Unwrap — Unexpectedly Found Nil&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This fatal error occurs whenever the &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; (force unwrap) operator is applied to an optional that holds &lt;code&gt;nil&lt;/code&gt;. The runtime terminates the app immediately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; operator tells the compiler &amp;ldquo;I guarantee this value is not nil.&amp;rdquo; If that guarantee is wrong, Swift crashes with a fatal error. Force unwraps are convenient but dangerous, especially with data from external sources. Replacing all force unwraps with safe alternatives is a key Swift best practice.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Swift Error — Key Not Found in Dictionary</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/dictionary-key/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/dictionary-key/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="key-not-found-in-dictionary"&gt;Key Not Found in Dictionary&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when you force-unwrap a dictionary subscript for a key that doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist, or when iterating over keys that have been removed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dictionaries in Swift return optionals when accessed by subscript. If you force-unwrap (&lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt;) the result and the key doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist, the runtime crashes. This is common with misspelled keys, keys from external data, or assumptions about dictionary contents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common patterns:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Swift Error — Unexpectedly Found Nil</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/unexpected-nil/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/unexpected-nil/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="unexpectedly-found-nil"&gt;Unexpectedly Found Nil&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a nil value is encountered in a context that expects a non-nil value, typically during force-unwrapping or forced type casting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Swift&amp;rsquo;s type system uses optionals to represent the absence of a value. When you bypass nil-checking with &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;as!&lt;/code&gt;, you risk a runtime crash if the value is actually nil. This error message can appear in various force-unwrap contexts including dictionary access, optional chaining failures, and API response handling.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Swift Error — Unexpectedly Found Nil While Unwrapping</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/nil-unwrapping/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/nil-unwrapping/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="unexpectedly-found-nil-while-unwrapping"&gt;Unexpectedly Found Nil While Unwrapping&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when you force-unwrap (&lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt;) an optional value that is &lt;code&gt;nil&lt;/code&gt;. Swift crashes at runtime instead of allowing nil to propagate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Optionals in Swift can hold either a value or &lt;code&gt;nil&lt;/code&gt;. When you use the &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; operator to force-unwrap, you tell the compiler you&amp;rsquo;re certain the value is non-nil. If you&amp;rsquo;re wrong, the runtime halts with this error. This commonly happens with unvalidated network responses, dictionary lookups, and incomplete initialization.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Swift Nil Unwrap — Unexpectedly Found Nil Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/nil-unwrap/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/nil-unwrap/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="nil-unwrap--unexpectedly-found-nil"&gt;Nil Unwrap — Unexpectedly Found Nil&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A nil unwrap crash occurs when you force-unwrap (&lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt;) an optional that holds &lt;code&gt;nil&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Swift optionals represent values that may be absent. Force unwrapping with &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; tells the compiler the value is guaranteed non-nil. If that guarantee is wrong, Swift crashes immediately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Force unwrapping nil optionals&lt;/strong&gt; — using &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; on nil value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Force try on throwing function&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;try!&lt;/code&gt; when function throws&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Implicitly unwrapped optionals&lt;/strong&gt; — accessing IUO before initialization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;API data&lt;/strong&gt; — force unwrapping optional response data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Force unwrapping nil&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; name: String? = &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nil&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;print(name!) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Fatal error: Unexpectedly found nil&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Force try&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; data = &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt;! JSONDecoder().decode(MyType.&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;, from: badData) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Fatal error&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Implicitly unwrapped optional&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; view: UIView!
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;view.addSubview(UIButton()) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Fatal error before load&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Force unwrapping optional chain&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; dict: [String: [Int]] = [&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;a&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: [&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;]]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; value = dict[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;b&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Fatal error&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-optional-binding"&gt;Fix 1: Use optional binding&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; name: String? = &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nil&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;print(name!) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Crash&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; name = name {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(name)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Name is nil&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-guard-statement"&gt;Fix 2: Use guard statement&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; url = URL(string: input)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;guard&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; url = URL(string: input) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Invalid URL&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-nil-coalescing"&gt;Fix 3: Use nil coalescing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; name: String? = &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nil&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;print(name!) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Crash&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; name: String? = &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nil&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;print(name ?? &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Unknown&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-optional-chaining"&gt;Fix 4: Use optional chaining&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; dict: [String: [Int]] = [:]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; value = dict[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;a&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Crash&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; value = dict[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;a&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;]?.first &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// nil, no crash&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: Safe URL parsing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; input = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;not a url&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; url = URL(string: input) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(url)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Invalid URL&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 2: Safe dictionary access&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; scores: [String: Int] = [&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;math&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;95&lt;/span&gt;]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; mathScore = scores[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;math&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;] ?? &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; scienceScore = scores[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;science&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;] ?? &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/force-unwrap/"&gt;Force Unwrap Crash&lt;/a&gt; — bang operator on nil&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/unexpected-nil/"&gt;Unexpectedly Found Nil&lt;/a&gt; — nil in unexpected context&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/array-index/"&gt;Array Index Out of Range&lt;/a&gt; — index beyond bounds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] TypeScript TS2532 v2 — Object Is Possibly Undefined Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2532-error-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2532-error-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="ts2532--object-is-possibly-undefined-v2"&gt;TS2532 — Object Is Possibly Undefined (v2)&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This variant of TS2532 covers scenarios involving async results, optional object properties, and Promise unwrapping where values may be &lt;code&gt;undefined&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common error messages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;TS2532: Object is possibly 'undefined'&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;TS2532: 'name' is possibly 'undefined'&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;TS2532: Cannot access 'property' because value is being used before being assigned&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TypeScript enforces that &lt;code&gt;undefined&lt;/code&gt; is checked before property access. This prevents &lt;code&gt;TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined&lt;/code&gt; at runtime.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] TypeScript TS2761 — X can only be declared as optional property</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2761-x-must-be-optional/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2761-x-must-be-optional/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="ts2761--x-can-only-be-declared-as-optional-property"&gt;TS2761 — &amp;lsquo;X&amp;rsquo; can only be declared as optional property&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TS2761 occurs when a property in an intersection type is required in one type but optional in another, creating a conflict.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Conflicting optional/required in intersection
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;A&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;B&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name?&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;C&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;A&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2761: &amp;#39;name&amp;#39; can only be optional
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Partial &amp;amp; required conflict
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Strict&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;id&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;number&lt;/span&gt; };
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Loose&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;id?&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt; };
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Both&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Strict&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Loose&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2761
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Merged interfaces with different optionality
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Base&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;value&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Extended&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;value?&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;number&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Merged&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Base&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Extended&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2761
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-make-properties-consistent"&gt;Fix 1: Make properties consistent&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;A&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name?&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;B&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name?&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;C&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;A&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// OK — both optional
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-union-type-instead"&gt;Fix 2: Use union type instead&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Result&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;A&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// union, not intersection
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-separate-conflicting-properties"&gt;Fix 3: Separate conflicting properties&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Combined&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;altName?&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2322-type/"&gt;TS2322: Type not assignable&lt;/a&gt; — general type mismatch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2741-property/"&gt;TS2741: Property is missing in type&lt;/a&gt; — missing property.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2356-destructuring/"&gt;TS2356: Type has no properties in common&lt;/a&gt; — incompatible types.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Java NullPointerException — Null Reference Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/nullpointerexception/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/nullpointerexception/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="nullpointerexception--null-reference-fix"&gt;NullPointerException — Null Reference Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;NullPointerException&lt;/code&gt; (NPE) is thrown when your code attempts to access a method or field on a reference that points to &lt;code&gt;null&lt;/code&gt;. It is the single most common exception in Java and almost always signals a bug — either a missing null check or an unexpected null return value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NPE fires at the exact point where you dereference a null reference. Common variants include:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>